The paper deals with content-based image retrieval, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Radon barcodes and single projections is a novel approach to this problem, which could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of weak learners, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The large dataset used in the experiments suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the subfield of big data (cs.DS), and the use of image features could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM).
